  levelNumber: 17
  levelName: Copan
  location: Copan, Honduras
  levelDescription: "Where kings carved history in stone, Cop\xE1n shines as the
    Maya\u2019s city of glyphs.\n\nLocated in western Honduras near the Guatemalan
    border, was one of the most important Maya capitals during the Classic Period
    (c. 400\u2013900 AD). Known for its artistry and scholarship, Cop\xE1n became
    a center of astronomy, hieroglyphic writing, and sculpture.\r\n\r\nThe city is
    famous for its Hieroglyphic Stairway, the longest known Maya inscription, carved
    with over 2,000 glyphs that record dynastic history. Cop\xE1n also features richly
    decorated temples, ballcourts, and stelae portraying its rulers, especially King
    Uaxaclajuun Ub\u2019aah K\u2019awiil (18 Rabbit), who oversaw its golden age.\r\n\r\nDespite
    later decline, Cop\xE1n\u2019s legacy endures as a UNESCO World Heritage Site,
    admired for its detailed carvings and monumental architecture that reveal the
    intellectual and spiritual life of the Maya."
